Toadstomp's Brewing Journal<br>
<br>
I took Brewing up from 0 to 155 in about two days.  This was all done with Wisdom at 130 - other stats should not make any difference to skillup rate, and no stat modified the success rate other than the level of the tradeskill.<br>
<br>
Purchasing and selling was done with CHA at 95 and faction at indifferent.  Comparisons with a mule at 105 CHA showed only a few copper pieces different, so the values here are very close to optimal.<br>
<br>
I am not able to forage, so these are all non-foraged recipes.  All ingredients are available in West and East Freeport.<br>
<br>
For the first step, I just bought the snake scales from vendors in West Freeport where the newbies sell them - sure you can hunt them down yourself but that would take too much time.<br>
<br>
Ingredient costs in pp:<br>
Snake Scales 0.011, Barley 0.016, Hops 0.016, Malt 0.016, Yeast 0.016, Short Beer 0.016, Mead 0.055, Gnomish Spirits 0.065, Dwarven Ale 0.071, Elven Wine 0.071, Flask Of Water 0.010, Bottle 0.005, Cask 0.033<br>
<br>
Sale price of recipe results to vendor:<br>
Bog Juice 0.023, Short Beer 0.014, Mead 0.046, Short Ale 0.046, Ale 0.027, Ol' Tujim's Fierce Brew 0.051, Double Brewed Double Stout Dwarven Ale 0.087, Faydwer Shaker 0.221<br>
<br>
